UPDATE materials SET description = 'Remove and dispose of all existing roofing materials down to the bare deck. A shingle tear-off is the complete removal of existing roofing materials—shingles, underlayment, flashing, and nails—down to the wood deck before installing a new roof. This process ensures a clean, stable surface, allows for inspection of the deck for rot, and ensures the new roof lasts longer.' WHERE name = 'Tear Off';

-- Standing Seam Painted items
UPDATE materials SET description = 'Remove old roof and install new metal roofing panels for superior durability and weather resistance. 1" SnapLok panels are 24-gauge standing seam metal roofing featuring a concealed fastener, snap-together design for easy installation. Typically made from durable Galvalume steel, they offer high wind/fire resistance with a 1-inch, 1.5-inch, or higher profile. These panels are ideal for residential and commercial roofs with a 3/12 or higher pitch.' WHERE name = '1" SnapLok Panels 24ga';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Dump fees, or "tipping fees," are charges imposed by landfills, transfer stations, or waste facilities for disposing of waste materials. Typically calculated by weight (per ton) or volume. Costs generally range from $40 to over $100 per ton, depending on the material type (e.g., C&D vs. municipal solid waste) and location.' WHERE name = 'Dump Fees';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Specialized fasteners used to secure metal panels to the roof deck for a watertight seal. #12 x 1.5" pancake screws are self-drilling or self-tapping fasteners featuring a low-profile, wide-bearing head, commonly used to attach metal roof clips to metal or wood studs. These high-strength screws, often made of hardened steel or 410 stainless, prevent panel damage due to their flat head.' WHERE name = 'Pancake Screws #12 x 1.5"';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Waterproof barrier installed over the roof deck beneath the shingles as a secondary layer of leak protection. Polyglass Polystick XFR is a self-adhered, waterproofing underlayment featuring patented Burn-Shield Technology™ for superior fire and ember resistance. Designed for high-temperature applications (up to 265°F), it is ideal for metal roofing and holds a UL Class A fire rating. It features a slip-resistant film, can be exposed for up to 180 days, and is suitable for WUI zones.' WHERE name = 'Polyglass XFR Underlayment';

UPDATE materials SET description = '10.5ft eave trim. SnapLok eave trim is a specialized, factory-formed metal flashing designed for standing seam roof systems, acting as a drip edge at the lower roof edge. It secures the bottom of the panels, protects the deck from water infiltration, and provides a clean, finished appearance for the Snap Lok system.' WHERE name = 'SnapLok Eave Trim';

UPDATE materials SET description = '10 ft hip cap. A SnapLok hip cap is a specialized, fastener-free roofing component designed for standing seam metal roofs. It uses a hidden, interlocking, or snap-together mechanism that fits securely onto metal filler strips (or cleats) between panels, preventing water infiltration while providing a clean, sleek, and durable finish without exposed screws.' WHERE name = 'SnapLok Hip Cap';

UPDATE materials SET description = '10.5ft rake trim. SnapLok rake trim (or gable trim) is a specialized, often fastener-free flashing used in standing seam metal roofing to seal the sloped roof edge (rake). It snaps onto a pre-installed cleat for a secure, watertight finish that prevents leaks, covers the top edge of roof panels, and provides a clean, finished appearance.' WHERE name = 'SnapLok Rake Trim';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Rubber-sealed flashing fitted around plumbing vent pipes to prevent leaks at roof penetrations. A Stainless Steel (SS) Pipe Boot is a durable, corrosion-resistant roof flashing designed to create a watertight seal around pipe penetrations, such as plumbing vents or HVAC exhaust. Featuring a rigid metal sleeve and base, it serves as a long-lasting alternative to rubber boots, preventing leaks by resisting cracks, rust, and UV degradation.' WHERE name = 'SS Pipe Boot';

-- 5V Mill Finish items
UPDATE materials SET description = 'Adhesive sealing tape applied at panel overlaps for a weathertight bond between metal panels. 1" butyl tape is a highly adhesive, synthetic rubber-based sealant that remains permanently flexible and tacky, providing an air- and watertight barrier. It is typically used for, but not limited to, sealing RV windows, metal roofing joints, and boat fittings. It is resistant to water, temperature changes, and vibration.' WHERE name = 'Butyl Tape 1"';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Foam or rubber sealing strips installed at panel edges to block wind-driven rain, insects, and debris. Eave closure strips are sealing components, typically made of foam or metal, installed at the eave line of a roof to close gaps between the roof deck and panels or tiles. They act as a barrier against insects, pests, and water infiltration, while also providing structural support, proper rise for tiles, and a secure finish to prevent wind-driven debris.' WHERE name = 'Eave Closure Strip';

UPDATE materials SET description = '10ft metal hip cap. A metal hip cap is specialized flashing installed over the diagonal ridge where two roof slopes meet (a hip) to create a watertight, finished seal. These V-shaped or custom-bent metal trims protect the most vulnerable parts of a roof from water infiltration, wind, and debris, often featuring hemmed edges for added strength.' WHERE name = 'Metal Hip Cap';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Rubber-sealed flashing fitted around plumbing vent pipes to prevent leaks at roof penetrations. Metal pipe boots are durable, watertight flashing assemblies designed to seal plumbing vents, HVAC pipes, and other penetrations on metal roofs. They feature flexible, often EPDM or silicone, collars with malleable aluminum or metal bases that conform to ribbed panels, preventing leaks while allowing for thermal expansion.' WHERE name = 'Metal Pipe Boot';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Specially shaped shingles installed along the peak and hip lines of your roof for a finished, watertight seal. A metal ridge cap is a crucial flashing component installed along the peak of a roof where two slopes meet, providing a watertight seal that protects against rain, snow, pests, and wind. Made of steel or aluminum, these 10-12 foot sections secure the top panels and often facilitate ventilation to prevent moisture buildup.' WHERE name = 'Metal Ridge Cap';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Specialized fasteners used to secure metal panels to the roof deck for a watertight seal.' WHERE name = 'Pancake Screws #10 x 1"';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'High Temp - Fire Rated Peel N Stick. Polystick® XFR by Polyglass is a premium, self-adhered waterproofing underlayment designed for steep-slope roofs, offering superior fire and ember resistance. It utilizes Burn-Shield Technology and ADESO® dual-compound self-adhered technology, featuring a fiberglass-reinforced SBS modified bitumen membrane that withstands temperatures up to 265°F and allows 180-day UV exposure.' WHERE name = 'Polyglass XFR';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Foam or rubber sealing strips installed at panel edges to block wind-driven rain, insects, and debris at the ridge line.' WHERE name = 'Ridge Closure Strip';

UPDATE materials SET description = 'Professionally install new roofing materials per manufacturer specifications to maintain full warranty coverage. 24-gauge 5V metal roof panels are a heavy-duty, exposed-fastener roofing system featuring 5 distinct "V" ribs, 24" wide coverage, and a 1/2" rib height. Known for durability and "old Florida" style, these 24ga panels are thicker and more impact/wind-resistant than 26ga, making them ideal for high-wind coastal areas, residential, or commercial projects.' WHERE name = 'Panel Install';
